						               													<description>A 2-player skirmish game based on the Star Frontiers Space Combat System - Knight Hawks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The gameboard is an 8 X 8 square grid which can be populated with terrain characteristics (asteroid, nebula, planets) at the discretion of the players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players share a common deck of cards comprising four types of card: Attack, Defence, Movement and Special.  Movement and Attack cards will have a specified range and all cards have a specified effect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players use counters or miniatures to represent the ships of their space fleets.  The number and types of ships utilised will be dependent and which of the 5 scenarios is used and on the factions played.   There are two main Factions: United Planetary Federation (UPF) and Sathar Empire though certain scenarios use Mercenaries, Pirates and Home Defence Fleets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game board set up and victory conditions are scenario driven, but gameplay is conducted in the same manner regardless of scenario.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with 5 cards.  Players take turns with each turn comprising 3 phases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1.    Tactics Phase&amp;#10;-     Draw 5 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2.    Action Phase&amp;#10;-     You may play cards from your hand. &amp;#10;-     Use move cards to move a ship the indicated number of spaces.  Moves are orthogonal or diagonal.&amp;#10;-     Use attack cards to engage enemy units at the indicated range. All attacks do 1 point of damage. Attacks are orthogonal or diagonal.&amp;#10;-     Use defence cards to negate a target attack.  &amp;#10;-     Played cards are discarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3.    End Phase&amp;#10;-     Max hand size is 7 cards.  Discard excess cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each ship has a number of hits (1-12 dependant on class). If a ship has more damage on it than it has hits, it is destroyed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play continues until the victory conditions for the chosen scenario are achieved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
